<p>You can also encode state data and functional interfaces in enums in Java. An example of something I like to do is:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">public static enum ShooterState {
  CLIMB_STATE(() -&gt; 20),
  SHOOT_STATE(() -&gt; getAutoTraackingAngle());

  private DoubleSupplier angleProvider;
  private ShooterState(DoubleSupplier angleProvider) {
    this.angleProvider = angleProvider;
  } 
  public double getAngle() { 
    return angleProvider.get();
  }
}</code></pre>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":44,"updated_at":"2024-04-22T17:16:21.131Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":267,"readers_count":266,"score":143.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":463974,"topic_slug":"enums-and-subsytem-states","display_username":"Justus","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":38557,"username":"Bmongar","name":"Brad","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bmongar/{size}/228654_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":5}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49388,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Microsoft"},"post_url":"/t/enums-and-subsytem-states/463974/5","custom_user_title":"Microsoft","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":5}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":5,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3369616,"name":"Justus","username":"Jus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jus/{size}/198009_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-22T17:22:29.855Z","cooked":"<p>The way I would implement this is like</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">public class ShooterSubsystem {

  public static enum ShooterState {

    CLIMB_MODE {
      @Override
      void execute(ShooterSubsystem shooter) {
        shooter.angle = 20;
      }
    },

    AUTO_SHOOT {
      @Override
      void execute(ShooterSubsystem shooter) {
        shooter.angle = getAutoTrackingAngle();
      }
    };

    abstract void execute(ShooterSubsystem shooter);
  }

  private ShooterState state = State.AUTO_SHOOT;
  public void setState(ShooterState state) {
    this.state = state;
  }
  private double angle; // some field to use

  // call this every loop
  public void execute() {
    state.execute(this);

    // ... code to do motors and stuff  
    doSomethingWith(angle);
  }
}</code></pre>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":44,"updated_at":"2024-04-22T17:22:29.855Z","reply_count":3,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":244,"readers_count":243,"score":128.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":463974,"topic_slug":"enums-and-subsytem-states","display_username":"Justus","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":38557,"username":"Bmongar","name":"Brad","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bmongar/{size}/228654_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49388,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Microsoft"},"post_url":"/t/enums-and-subsytem-states/463974/6","custom_user_title":"Microsoft","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":3}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":3,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3369627,"name":"Amicus1","username":"Amicus1","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/a9adbd/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-04-22T17:27:10.199Z","cooked":"<p>What if these states need to run something on entrance or exit? For example, a “hold current angle” would need to measure the angle when the robot enters the holding state.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":44,"updated_at":"2024-04-22T17:27:10.199Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":202,"readers_count":201,"score":50.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":463974,"