lse,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":49388,"username":"Jus","name":"Justus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jus/{size}/198009_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":51496,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/enums-and-subsytem-states/463974/8","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3369646,"name":"","username":"uncoolin","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/uncoolin/{size}/224822_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-22T17:36:19.946Z","cooked":"<p>Implementing this using commands may be something to consider as well. Because only one command can be running on a subsystem at a time, they essentially act as a state machine like some of the ones you have here. Commands are fairly easy to implement if you have experience with them and streamline the state machine process significantly.</p>
<p>A simple method for this is having a command for each mode that you want the shooter to be in. You can schedule these commands based on what buttons the operator is pressing or other criteria. So long as each of these commands “requires” the subsystem, only one of these commands can be running at any given time. Then, you simply set the shooter angle in each command according to what you want the command to do.</p>
<p>The command-based method is also very useful because you can set default commands, which are just commands that always run when no other command that requires the subsystem it is linked to is scheduled. I’d highly recommend looking into some documentation and some examples of command-based programming for <span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span>.</p>
