<p>With your example of the LED subsystem, there could just be a single command that is always running and has logic inside of it that changes the LED state based on parameters from the other subsystems. Commands can have a lot of logic or just do singular things, as long as you string them together properly.</p>","post_number":13,"post_type":1,"posts_count":44,"updated_at":"2024-04-22T18:05:04.530Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":11,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":159,"readers_count":158,"score":51.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":463974,"topic_slug":"enums-and-subsytem-states","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":51496,"username":"woodworker2001","name":"Dan Langdon","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/w/bbe5ce/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":58518,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"3859 Software Lead"},"post_url":"/t/enums-and-subsytem-states/463974/13","custom_user_title":"3859 Software Lead","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3369884,"name":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","username":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/slab-mr.thomas/{size}/182153_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-22T19:48:12.038Z","cooked":"<p>Striving for a command to be a single state and making the command not rely on history or parameters is ideal for usability. How many different versions of essentially the same code is best before using parameters? Hard to say and there are <span class="abbreviation">CD<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Chief Delphi"></template></span> threads discussing that. We had six colors and rainbow in seven one-line methods. It was very easy to code, use, and understand by the whole team.</p>
<p>I don’t regret the “bloat” of a dozen extra lines of code if we can accurately, perfectly, correctly use the correct command in an instant in emergency changes between matches. Similarly it was easy to use at home while developing robot motions. This is “mistake-proofing” and it works.</p>
<p>In the LED subsystem:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public Command setBlueCommand()
    {
        return Commands.runOnce( () -&gt; setBlue(false)).withName("setBlue");
    }

public Command setPurpleCommand()
    {
        return Commands.runOnce( () -&gt; setPurple(false)).withName("setPurple");
    }
...
</code></pre>
<p>[Having a color command call an identically named non-command may be too redundant and could be subject to refactoring next season. The <code>false</code> is blink option.</p>
<p>Also, the students got so enthralled with lambda expressions (new to them) they often recoded the <code>runOnce</code> lambda instead of using the already coded command; more refactoring.</p>
<p>We do use parameters, in part, for the flywheel speeds and sometimes a dedicated method for a single speed. More refactoring to achieve consistency.]</p>","post_number":14,"post_type":1,"posts_count":44,"updated_at":"2024-04-22T19:48:12.038Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":13,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":149,"readers_count":148,"score":49.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":463974,"topic_slug":"enums-and-subsytem-states","display_username":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":58518,"username":"uncoolin","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/uncoolin/{size}/224822_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":24594,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/enums-and-subsytem-states/463974/14","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3369930,"name":"Justus","username":"Jus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jus/{size}/198009_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-22T20:16:58.342Z","cooked":"<p>Just add an abstract method for <code>onEnter</code> and <code>onExit</code> and override them in the enum definition. Here is update to use onEnter and onExit.</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">public class ShooterSubsystem {

  public static enum ShooterState {

    OFF { } // this is some default state

    CLIMB_MODE {
      @Override
      void execute(ShooterSubsystem shooter) {
        shooter.angle = 20;
      }
      @Override
      void onEnter(ShooterSubsystem shooter) {
         System.out.println("Entering climb mode");
      }
      @Override
      void onExit(ShooterSubsystem shooter) {
         System.out.println("Exiting climb mode");
      }

    },

    AUTO_SHOOT {
      @Override
      void execute(ShooterSubsystem shooter) {
        shooter.angle = getAutoTrackingAngle();
      }
      @Override
      void onEnter(ShooterSubsystem shooter) {
         System.out.println("Entering auto shoot mode");
      }
      @Override
      void onExit(ShooterSubsystem shooter) {
         System.out.println("Exiting auto shoot mode");
      }
    };

    abstract void execute(ShooterSubsystem shooter);
    abstract void onEnter(ShooterSubsystem shooter);
    abstract void onExit(ShooterSubsystem shooter);
  }

  private ShooterState state = State.AUTO_SHOOT; // set to some default 
  private ShooterState lastState = State.AUTO_SHOOT; 
  public void setState(ShooterState state) {
    this.state = state;
  }
  private double angle; // some field to use

  // call this every loop
  public void execute() {

    // if we are entering a new state
    if (state != lastState) {
      state.onExit(this);
      state.onEnter(this);
    }

    // continuous on the current state
    state.execute(this);

    // ... code to do motors and stuff  
    doSomethingWith(angle);
  }
}
</code></pre>","post_number":15,"post_type":1,"posts_count":44,"updated_at":"2024-04-22T20:16:58.342Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":136,"readers_count":135,"score":87.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":463974,"topic_slug":"enums-and-subsytem-states","display_username":"Justus","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":33946,"username":"Amicus1","name":"Amicus1","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/a9adbd/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49388,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Microsoft"},"post_url":"/t/enums-and-subsytem-states/463974/15","custom_user_title":"Microsoft","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3369967,"name":"Gavin Matthews","username":"bovlb","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bovlb/{size}/167232_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-22T20:35:36.386Z","cooked":"<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="Jus" data-post="15" data-topic="463974">
